description: An avocado is a bright green fruit with a large pit and dark leathery skin. They're also known as alligator pears or butter fruit. Avocados are a favorite of the produce section. They're the go-to ingredient for guacamole dips. And they're turning up in everything from salads and wraps to smoothies and even brownies

Fat equals flavor, but the protein content is important, too: Goat milk is lower in casein, a protein that curdles, so it produces a more crumbly curd, while sheep's cheese is generally more cohesive. Sheep cheese is also higher in carbs, vitamin C, vitamin B12, folate, calcium, and magnesium than goat cheese

Corn the cob is the culinary term for a cooked ear of freshly-picked maize from a cultivar of sweet corn. The ear is picked while the endosperm is in the 'milk stage' so that the kernels are still tender.
